== Postage stamps issue == The Libyan state-owned [[General Posts and Telecommunications Company]] (GPTC) dedicated a [[postage stamps]] issue to ''Ghadafi Prize for Human Rights'' in 1994 (date of issue December 31). The issue consists of a minisheet with sixteen stamps.
Each horizontal strip of four stamps is dedicated to a particular subject: * [[Nelson Mandela]] * [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas]] * [[Bosnian War]] * [[First Intifada|Intifada]] in Palestine
